<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgaseaduse eesm&auml;rk ja rakendusala </eesti>
<inglise>Objective and area of application of Wages Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Palgaseadus m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tavate isikute t&ouml;&ouml;tasustamise ning neile t&ouml;&ouml;tasuga seotud tagatiste andmise ja h&uuml;vituste maksmise &otilde;igusliku korralduse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Wages Act determines the legal regulation of the remuneration of persons who work under an employment contract, the grant of guarantees and payment of compensation relating to remuneration. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Palgaseaduse rakendamise erisused majandusharudes (tegevusaladel) m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks seadustega v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Specifications in the application of the Wages Act for particular sectors of the economy (areas of activity) shall be determined by laws or regulations of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avalikele teenistujatele laieneb k&auml;esolev seadus niiv&otilde;rd, kuiv&otilde;rd avalikku teenistust reguleeriva v&otilde;i muu seadusega ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This Act extends to public servants unless otherwise provided by an Act regulating public service or other Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Palk on tasu, mida t&ouml;&ouml;andja maksab t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml; eest vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;lepingule v&otilde;i &otilde;igusaktile, samuti muudel &otilde;igusakti, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Wages are the remuneration which an employer pays to an employee for work performed in accordance with an employment contract, legal instrument or in other cases prescribed by legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Palk koosneb p&otilde;hipalgast ja seaduses etten&auml;htud juhtudel makstavatest lisatasudest, preemiatest ja juurdemaksetest. </eesti>
<inglise>Wages are comprised of basic wages and additional remuneration, bonuses and additional payments paid in the cases prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&otilde;hipalk on t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus v&otilde;i &otilde;igusaktis kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratud tunni-, p&auml;eva-, n&auml;dala- v&otilde;i kuupalgam&auml;&auml;ra alusel arvutatud palk. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Basic wages are wages calculated on the basis of an hourly, daily, weekly or monthly rate determined in an employment contract or legal instrument. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Seaduses, haldusaktis, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud juhtudel maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale peale p&otilde;hipalga lisatasu v&otilde;i juurdemakseid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In the cases prescribed by law, administrative legislation, a collective agreement or employment contract, an employer shall, in addition to basic wages, pay additional remuneration or additional payment to an employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Lisatasu on summa, mida t&ouml;&ouml;andja maksab t&ouml;&ouml;tajale p&otilde;hipalgale lisaks t&auml;iendavate t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmise v&otilde;i n&otilde;utavast tulemuslikuma t&ouml;&ouml; eest v&otilde;i muudel &otilde;igusaktis, kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud juhtudel, samuti preemiana t&ouml;&ouml;andja &uuml;hepoolse otsuse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Additional payment is an amount which an employer pays in addition to basic wages to an employee for the performance of additional duties or for more effective work than required or in other cases prescribed by a legal instrument, collective or employment contract and also as a bonus on the basis of an unilateral decision of an employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Juurdemakse on summa, mida t&ouml;&ouml;andja maksab t&ouml;&ouml;tajale selleks, et tagada talle etten&auml;htud palgatase ja h&uuml;vitada v&otilde;imalik palga v&auml;henemine. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Additional payment is an amount which an employer pays to an employee in order to guarantee the wage level prescribed for him or her or to compensate for a possible reduction in wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Keskmine palk on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal teatud aja jooksul teenitud palga kogusummast arvutatav keskmine tasu mingi aja&uuml;hiku (tunni, p&auml;eva, n&auml;dala, kuu vms.) kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Average wages are the average remuneration per unit of time (hour, day, week, month, etc.) calculated based on the gross wages earned by an employee during a specific period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>Keskmise palga arvutamise kord s&auml;testatakse Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for calculation of average wages shall be established by a regulation of the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Palga alamm&auml;&auml;r on Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt kehtestatud kindlale aja&uuml;hikule (tunnile, p&auml;evale, n&auml;dalale, kuule vms.) vastav palga suurus, millest madalamas ei ole lubatud kokku leppida t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel t&auml;ist&ouml;&ouml;ajaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The minimum wage is the minimum amount of wage per specific unit of time (hour, day, week, month, etc.) established by the Government of the Republic which may be agreed upon for full-time employment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgatingimuste m&otilde;iste ja kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Definition and determination of wage conditions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Palgatingimustena k&auml;sitatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses palgam&auml;&auml;rasid, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale makstavaid lisatasusid ja juurdemakseid, palga arvutamise viise ja maksmise korda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In this Act, wage rates, additional remuneration and additional payments payable to employees, methods of calculation and procedures for payment of wages are deemed to be wage conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja palgatingimused ja nende muudatused m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Wage conditions of employees and amendments thereto shall be determined by employment contracts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgatingimuste muutmine </eesti>
<inglise>Changing of wage conditions </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kokkulepitud palgatingimusi on lubatud muuta ainult poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Wage conditions which have been agreed in an employment contract may be changed only by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Palka korraldavate seaduste, valitsuse m&auml;&auml;ruste, kollektiivlepingu v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu muutumisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud muutma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate palgatingimusi hiljemalt &uuml;he kuu m&ouml;&ouml;dumisel, kohaldades neid &otilde;igusakti kehtima hakkamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon amendment of an Act regulating wages, a regulation of the Government, a collective agreement or employment contract, an employer is required to amend the wage conditions of employees within not less than one month and to apply such conditions from the date the legislation enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga seadusevastane v&auml;hendamine v&otilde;i suurendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Unlawful reduction or increase in wages </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud on palka suurendada v&otilde;i v&auml;hendada olenevalt t&ouml;&ouml;taja soost, rahvusest, nahav&auml;rvist, rassist, emakeelest, sotsiaalsest p&auml;ritolust, &uuml;hiskondlikust seisundist, varasemast tegevusest, usulistest, poliitilistest v&otilde;i muudest veendumustest ja suhtumisest kaitsev&auml;eteenistuskohustusse. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to increase or reduce wages on the grounds of an employee's sex, nationality, colour, race, native language, social origin, social status, previous activities, religion, political or other opinion, or attitude towards the duty to serve in the armed forces. </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud on palka v&auml;hendada olenevalt perekonnaseisust, perekondlikest kohustustest, kuuluvusest kodanike &uuml;hendustesse ning t&ouml;&ouml;tajate v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;andjate huvide esindamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited to reduce wages on the grounds of the marital status, family obligations, membership in citizens' associations or representation of the interests of employees or employers. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;te </eesti>
<inglise>Principle of equal remuneration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Keelatud on kehtestada eri soost t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele sama v&otilde;i v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rse t&ouml;&ouml; eest erinevaid palgatingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The establishment of different wage conditions for the same or equal work to employees of different sex is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on t&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udmisel kohustatud t&otilde;endama, et ta on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud p&otilde;him&otilde;tet j&auml;rginud ja eeliste andmine on tingitud soost s&otilde;ltumatutest objektiivsetest asjaoludest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of an employee, the employer is required to prove that the employer has adhered to the principle specified in subsection (1) of this section and any preferences given were based on objective circumstances not connected to sex. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda selgitusi palga arvutamise aluste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Employees have the right to request explanations concerning the bases for calculation of wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda sama v&otilde;i v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rse t&ouml;&ouml; eest v&otilde;rdset tasustamist ning v&otilde;rdse tasustamise p&otilde;him&otilde;tte rikkumisega tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employee has the right to demand equal payment for the same or equal work and the compensation of damages caused by violation of the principle of equal remuneration. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitise suuruse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramisel arvestatakse ebav&otilde;rdse tasustamise kestust, ulatust ja laadi. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon determination of compensation, the duration, extent and nature of unequal remuneration shall be taken into consideration. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud teavitama t&ouml;&ouml;tajat t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;tmisel v&otilde;rdse tasustamise &otilde;iguslikust regulatsioonist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon hiring, employers are required to inform employees of the regulation of equal remuneration by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga arvutamine ja maksmine rahas </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation and payment of wages in money </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale arvutatakse ja makstakse palka rahas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Wages shall be calculated and shall be paid to employees in money. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Soodsamate palgatingimuste kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of more favourable wage conditions </inglise>
<eesti>Kollektiivlepingus v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ette n&auml;ha seaduses kehtestatuga v&otilde;rreldes soodsamad palgatingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>A collective agreement or employment contract may prescribe more favourable wage conditions to an employee than those established by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmete avaldamine t&ouml;&ouml;taja palga kohta </eesti>
<inglise>Disclosure of information concerning wages of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud andma t&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil andmeid temale arvutatud ja makstud v&otilde;i maksmisele kuuluva palga kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer is required to give an employee information concerning wages calculated and paid or payable to him or her at his or her request. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Palga maksmisel on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud andma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kirjaliku teatise talle arvutatud palga koostisosade (p&otilde;hipalga, lisatasude, preemia ja juurdemaksete), samuti tema palgast kinnipeetud summade, sellest makstud maksude ja tema nimel tehtud sissemaksete kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon payment of wages, an employer is required to give an employee a written notice concerning the component parts of the wages calculated to him or her (basic wages, additional remuneration, bonus and additional payments), and the amounts deducted from his or her wages including taxes paid on the wages and contributions made in the employee's name. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole &otilde;igust ilma t&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;usolekuta v&otilde;i seadusest tuleneva aluseta avaldada andmeid t&ouml;&ouml;tajale arvutatud, makstud v&otilde;i maksmisele kuuluva palga kohta, samuti palgatingimuste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer does not have the right to disclose information concerning the wages calculated, paid or payable to an employee or information concerning the employee's wage conditions without the consent of the employee or basis arising from the law. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(3 (1)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 toodud keeld ei kehti korruptsioonivastase seaduse (RT I 1999, 16, 276; 87, 791; 2000, 25, 145; 2001, 58, 357) &sect;-s 4 nimetatud ametiisikute palga kohta ning neil juhtudel, kui andmeid n&otilde;uab kohus, prokuratuur, kohtueelse uurimise asutus, Maksuamet, Riigikontroll, Statistikaamet v&otilde;i T&ouml;&ouml;inspektsioon, samuti seadusega etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3 (1)) The prohibition set out in subsection (3) of this section does not apply to the wages of officials specified in &sect; 4 of the Anti-corruption Act (RT I 1999, 16, 276; 87, 791; 2000, 25, 145; 2001, 58, 357), in cases where information is required by a court, the Prosecutor's Office, a pre-trial investigation authority, the Tax Board, the Statistical Office, the Labour Inspectorate or the State Audit Office, or in cases prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>Korruptsioonivastase seaduse &sect;-s 4 nimetatud ametiisikute palga kohta andmete avalikustamise korra ja tingimused kehtestab rahandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The procedure for and conditions of disclosure of information concerning the wages of the officials specified in &sect; 4 of this Act shall be established by the Minister of Financial Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(3 (2)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 (1) s&auml;testatut rakendatakse samuti korruptsioonivastase seaduse &sect;-s 4 nimetatud riigi, kohaliku omavalitsuse v&otilde;i avalik-&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku osalusega &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhatuse v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liikmele, riigi- v&otilde;i munitsipaalvara v&otilde;i muu avalik-&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku vara &uuml;leandmist otsustava organi liikmele makstavate tasude suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>(3 (2)) The provisions of subsection (3 (1)) of this section also apply with regard to remuneration paid to members of the management boards or supervisory boards of companies in which the state, a local government or a legal person in public law has a holding or to members of bodies which decide on the transfer of state or municipal assets or the assets of other legal persons in public law. </inglise>
<eesti>(09.05.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 40, 248) </eesti>
<inglise>(09.05.2000 entered into force 01.07.2000 - RT I 2000, 40, 248) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;andjal on &otilde;igus avaldada t&ouml;&ouml;tajate r&uuml;hmade (mitte v&auml;hem kui viis t&ouml;&ouml;tajat) palgaandmeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employer has the right to disclose information concerning the wages of groups of employees (not less than five employees). </inglise>
<eesti>II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter II </inglise>
<eesti>Palgam&auml;&auml;rade ja palgas&uuml;steemide kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of Wage Rates and Wage Systems </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgam&auml;&auml;rade kehtestamine ettev&otilde;ttes, asutuses v&otilde;i muus organisatsioonis </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of wage rates in enterprises, agencies or other organisations </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja kehtestab palgam&auml;&auml;rad vastavalt t&ouml;&ouml;de erinevusele ja t&ouml;&ouml;tingimustele, l&auml;htudes t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate vahel s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepingust. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer shall establish wage rates according to the differences in work and working conditions, based on a collective agreement entered into between the employer and employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja palgam&auml;&auml;ra kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Determination of wage rate of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja palgam&auml;&auml;r m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu s&otilde;lmimisel poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The wage rate of an employee shall be determined by agreement of the parties upon entering into an employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Palgam&auml;&auml;ra muudetakse poolte kokkuleppel, samuti palga alamm&auml;&auml;ra muutmise korral, kui kehtestatud palga alamm&auml;&auml;r osutub madalamaks Vabariigi Valitsuse poolt v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga kehtestatust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Wage rates shall be amended by agreement of the parties and upon amendment of the minimum wage if the minimum wage established is lower than the minimum wage established by the Government of the Republic or a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgas&uuml;steemide kehtestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Establishment of wage system </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja kehtestab palgas&uuml;steemid (tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; eest tasu arvutamise viisid), arvestades s&otilde;lmitud kollektiivlepinguid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer shall establish a wage system (methods of calculation of remuneration for work performed) taking into consideration collective agreements which have been entered into. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>III peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter III </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tasustamine eritingimustes </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration under Special Conditions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisat&ouml;&ouml; tasustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration for additional work </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja teeb talle kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml; ajal t&ouml;&ouml;andja taotlusel t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htuga v&otilde;rreldes lisat&ouml;&ouml;d, suurendatakse tema palka v&otilde;i makstakse talle lisatasu poolte kokkuleppega kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud suuruses. </eesti>
<inglise>If, upon the request of an employer, an employee performs additional work during determined working hours as compared with work prescribed in the employment contract, his or her wages shall be increased or additional remuneration paid in an amount determined by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasustamine t&ouml;&ouml; eest, milles t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ei ole kokku lepitud </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration for work not agreed on in employment contract </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja teeb kokkuleppel t&ouml;&ouml;andjaga t&ouml;&ouml;d, mida t&ouml;&ouml;leping ette ei n&auml;e, ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja on vabastatud selleks ajaks oma t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguj&auml;rgsete t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest, makstakse talle selle t&ouml;&ouml; eest tasu poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>If an employee, by agreement with an employer, performs work which is not prescribed in an employment contract and the employee is released from his or her contractual duties for that time, he or she shall be remunerated for such work by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; tasustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration for overtime </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; eest lisatasu maksmine v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitamine vaba aja andmisega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks poolte kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Additional remuneration for overtime or compensation by time off in lieu of money shall be determined by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;letunnit&ouml;&ouml; iga tunni eest t&ouml;&ouml;tajale makstav lisatasu ei tohi olla v&auml;iksem kui 50% selle t&ouml;&ouml;taja tunnipalga m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Additional remuneration per hour of overtime paid to an employee shall not be less than 50 per cent of the hourly wage rate of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Puhkep&auml;evadel t&ouml;&ouml;tamise h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for work on days off </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja graafikuv&auml;line t&ouml;&ouml;tamine temale etten&auml;htud puhkep&auml;evadel h&uuml;vitatakse poolte kokkuleppel kas rahas v&otilde;i vaba aja andmisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unscheduled work by an employee on his or her prescribed days off shall be compensated for by agreement of the parties either in money or time off in lieu of money. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;tamise h&uuml;vitamisel rahas makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;l oldud aja eest lisatasu v&auml;hemalt 50% tema palga m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If compensation for work on days off is paid in money, the employee shall be additionally remunerated for time worked on days off in an amount equal to at least 50 per cent of his or her wage rate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Puhkep&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;tamise h&uuml;vitamisel vaba aja andmisega tasutakse puhkep&auml;eval tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; eest nagu tavalisel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If work on days off is compensated for by time off in lieu of money, work performed on a day off shall be remunerated for as work performed on an ordinary working day. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigip&uuml;hal tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; tasustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration for work performed on public holiday </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigip&uuml;hal tehtud t&ouml;&ouml; eest makstakse v&auml;hemalt kahekordselt, olenemata sellest, kas t&ouml;&ouml;tati graafikukohaselt v&otilde;i graafikuv&auml;liselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Work performed on a public holiday shall be remunerated at least at a double rate regardless of whether such work is scheduled or unscheduled. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui vahetus algab riigip&uuml;haeelsel p&auml;eval ja l&otilde;peb riigip&uuml;hal v&otilde;i algab riigip&uuml;hal ja l&otilde;peb riigip&uuml;haj&auml;rgsel p&auml;eval, tasustatakse t&ouml;&ouml;d sellises vahetuses nagu riigip&uuml;hal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If a shift begins on the day preceding a public holiday and ends on the public holiday or begins on a public holiday and ends on the day following the public holiday, work performed during the shift shall be remunerated for as work performed on a public holiday. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja soovil v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;andja h&uuml;vitada riigip&uuml;hal graafikuv&auml;list t&ouml;&ouml;tamist vaba aja andmisega t&ouml;&ouml;l oldud aja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) At the request of an employee, an employer may compensate for unscheduled work performed on a public holiday in time off in lieu of money to the extent of the time worked. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul tasustatakse riigip&uuml;hal tehtud t&ouml;&ouml;d nagu t&ouml;&ouml;d tavalisel t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case work performed on a public holiday shall be remunerated as work performed on an ordinary working day. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisatasu &otilde;htuse ja &ouml;&ouml;t&ouml;&ouml; eest </eesti>
<inglise>Additional remuneration for evening and night work </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml; eest &otilde;htusel ajal (kella 18-st kuni 22-ni) v&otilde;i &ouml;&ouml;sel (kella 22-st kuni 6-ni) makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale lisatasu v&otilde;i suurendatakse p&otilde;hipalka vastavalt poolte kokkuleppele. </eesti>
<inglise>Additional remuneration shall be paid for work performed in the evening (from 18.00 to 22.00) or at night (from 22.00 to 06.00) or basic wages shall be increased by agreement of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>Lisatasu iga t&ouml;&ouml;tunni eest &otilde;htusel ajal ei tohi olla v&auml;iksem kui 10% ja &ouml;&ouml;sel v&auml;iksem kui 20% t&ouml;&ouml;taja tunnipalga m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>Additional remuneration for each working hour in the evening shall not be less than 10 per cent and at night shall not be less than 20 per cent of the hourly wage rate of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasustamine t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration in case of failure to perform duties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei t&auml;ida t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannet oma s&uuml;&uuml;l, makstakse talle tasu vastavalt tehtud t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If an employee fails to perform duties by his or her own fault, the employee shall be remunerated according to work performed. </inglise>
<eesti>Ajapalgalisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajal, kes ei t&ouml;&ouml;ta normeeritud t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete alusel, ei v&auml;hendata ajapalgam&auml;&auml;ra t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise eest tingimusel, et ta on t&auml;itnud t&ouml;&ouml;aja normi. </eesti>
<inglise>The wage rate per unit of time of an employee remunerated on the basis of time worked who does not work on the basis of production standards shall not be reduced in the case of failure to perform duties if the employee has worked the standard working time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei saa t&auml;ita t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannet temast olenemata asjaoludel, maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja v&auml;ljateenitud palgale juurde ulatuses, millega palgaarvestusaja jooksul t&ouml;&ouml;l oldud aja eest oleks tagatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kokkulepitud palgam&auml;&auml;r. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employee cannot perform duties due to circumstances beyond his or her control, the employer shall, in addition to earned wages, pay wages to the extent to which the wage rate agreed on in the employment contract would have been guaranteed for time worked during the wage calculation period. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) (Kehtetu - 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(3) (Repealed - 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasustamine praagi korral </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration in case of defective work or products </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Praagiks loetakse t&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;i toodang, mis ei vasta t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt kehtestatud kvaliteedin&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Work or products which do not conform to the quality standards established by an employer are deemed to be defective work or products. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;ielik praak on t&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;i toodang, mis ei k&otilde;lba &uuml;ldse kasutamiseks etten&auml;htud otstarbel ja mida pole v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;i majanduslikult otstarbekas kasutamisk&otilde;lblikuks muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>Work or products which cannot be used for their intended purpose and which cannot be made usable or cannot be made usable in an economically efficient manner are wholly defective work or products. </inglise>
<eesti>Osaline praak on t&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;i toodang, mida m&otilde;ningate m&ouml;&ouml;ndustega on v&otilde;imalik etten&auml;htud otstarbel kasutada v&otilde;i mida on v&otilde;imalik ja otstarbekas t&auml;iendava t&ouml;&ouml;tlusega kasutamisk&otilde;lblikuks muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>Work or products which, with certain allowances, can be used for their intended purpose or which can and for which it is purposeful to be made usable with additional treatment are partially defective work or products. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Praaki p&otilde;hjustada v&otilde;ivate asjaolude ilmnemisel, samuti praagi tekkimisel on t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustatud sellest viivitamatult teatama t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If circumstances which may cause defective work or products arise, an employee is required to notify his or her employer or the employer's representative promptly thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral loetakse praak tekkinuks t&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon failure to perform this duty, the defective work or products are deemed to have arisen by the fault of the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja teatas k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud asjaoludest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale, too aga andis korralduse t&ouml;&ouml;d j&auml;tkata, tasutakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale edasise praagi eest nagu kvaliteetse toodangu (t&ouml;&ouml;) eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If an employee notifies an employer or the employer's representative of the circumstances specified in subsection (2) of this section but the employer or the employer's representative orders work to continue, the employee shall be remunerated for further defective work or products as for quality work or products. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;l tehtud t&auml;ieliku praagi eest tasu ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee shall not be remunerated for wholly defective work or products caused by his or her fault. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;l tehtud osalise praagi eest makstakse tasu alandatud m&auml;&auml;ral, s&otilde;ltuvalt t&ouml;&ouml; tulemuse k&otilde;lblikkuse astmest. </eesti>
<inglise>An employee shall be remunerated for partially defective work or products caused by his or her fault at a lowered rate depending on the degree to which the result of the work is usable. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;tamisel praagi tekkimises vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. ja 3. l&otilde;ikes kirjeldatud juhtudel pole s&uuml;&uuml;di t&ouml;&ouml;taja, makstakse talle tasu selle t&ouml;&ouml; tegemiseks etten&auml;htud aja eest v&auml;hemalt t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kokkulepitud palgam&auml;&auml;ra ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If an employee is not at fault for defective work or products in the cases specified in subsections (2) and (3) of this section, he or she shall be remunerated for the time prescribed for performing such work at least to the extent of the wage rate agreed on in the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasustamine t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku aja eest </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration for work stoppage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja s&uuml;&uuml;l tekkinud t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku aja eest talle tasu ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee shall not be remunerated for the time period of a work stoppage caused by his or her fault. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei ole s&uuml;&uuml;di t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku tekkimises ja on teatanud t&ouml;&ouml;seisakut esile kutsuda v&otilde;ivatest asjaoludest ning t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku algusest t&ouml;&ouml;andjale v&otilde;i tema esindajale, maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja talle t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku aja eest tasu kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus etten&auml;htud ulatuses, kuid mitte v&auml;hem t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kokkulepitud palgam&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If an employee is not at fault for a work stoppage and he or she has notified the employer or the employer's representative of circumstances which may cause a work stoppage and of the beginning of the work stoppage, the employer shall remunerate him or her to the extent prescribed in a collective agreement or employment contract, but not less than according to the wage rate agreed on in the employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga s&auml;ilitamine alatiseks &uuml;leviimisel teisele, v&auml;hemtasustatavale t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i &uuml;mberpaigutamisel teisele t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohale </eesti>
<inglise>Continuation of payment of wages upon permanent transfer to other, lower paid position or other workplace </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja alatiseks &uuml;leviimisel teisele, v&auml;hemtasustatavale t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i &uuml;mberpaigutamisel teisele t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohale t&ouml;&ouml;andja algatusel, kui selle t&otilde;ttu v&auml;heneb t&ouml;&ouml;taja palk temast mitteolenevatel p&otilde;hjustel, s&auml;ilitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale keskmine palk &uuml;he kuu jooksul, arvates &uuml;leviimise v&otilde;i &uuml;mberpaigutamise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>If an employee is permanently transferred to another, lower paid position or relocated to another workplace on the initiative of the employer and if the wages of the employee consequently decrease for reasons independent of him or her, the employee shall continue to receive his or her average wages for one month after the date of transfer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasustamine ajutise &uuml;leviimise korral teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le tootmish&auml;davajaduse t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration in case of temporary transfer to other position due to production emergency </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja ajutise &uuml;leviimise korral teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le tootmish&auml;davajaduse t&otilde;ttu makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale palka t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi, kuid mitte v&auml;hem keskmisest palgast endisel t&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon temporary transfer to other position due to production emergency, the employee is paid wages according to the position, but not less than his or her average wages in the former position. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasustamine ajutise &uuml;leviimise korral teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku t&otilde;ttu </eesti>
<inglise>Remuneration in case of temporary transfer to other position due to work stoppage </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes ei ole s&uuml;&uuml;di t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku tekkimises, makstakse teisel t&ouml;&ouml;l palka t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi, kuid mitte v&auml;hem keskmisest palgast endisel t&ouml;&ouml;l, kui ta t&auml;idab t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid etten&auml;htud mahus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee who is not at fault for a work stoppage is paid wages according to the other position but not less than his or her average wages in the former position, on condition that he or she performs his or her duties to the prescribed extent. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes ei t&auml;ida teisel t&ouml;&ouml;l t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid etten&auml;htud mahus temast mitteoleneval p&otilde;hjusel, makstakse palka t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi, kuid mitte v&auml;hem kokkulepitud palgam&auml;&auml;rast endisel t&ouml;&ouml;l. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employee who fails to perform his or her duties to the prescribed extent in the other position for reasons which do not depend on him or her shall be paid wages according to the other position, but not less than the wage rate agreed earlier in his or her former position. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes on s&uuml;&uuml;di t&ouml;&ouml;seisaku tekkimises v&otilde;i kes ei t&auml;ida t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid etten&auml;htud mahus, makstakse teisel t&ouml;&ouml;l palka t&ouml;&ouml; j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employee who is at fault for a work stoppage or who fails to perform his or her duties to the prescribed extent in the other position is paid wages according to the position. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Maanteeveo mootors&otilde;iduki juhi palga arvutamise ja maksmise eritingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Special conditions for calculation and payment of wages to drivers of goods road transport vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>Maanteeveo mootors&otilde;iduki juhile on keelatud arvutada ja maksta nii p&otilde;hipalka kui ka lisatasu l&auml;bitud kilomeetrite ning veetud kaubakoguse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The basic wages and additional remuneration of drivers of goods road transport vehicles shall not be calculated or paid on the basis of the kilometres covered or the amount of transported goods. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandina v&otilde;ib l&auml;bitud kilomeetreid v&otilde;i kaubakogust arvesse v&otilde;tta lisatasu maksmisel, kui selle arvutamise viis, tingimused ja m&auml;&auml;rad on sellised, mis ei soodusta ohutu liikluse n&otilde;uete eiramist ning on kollektiivlepingus ette n&auml;htud. </eesti>
<inglise>As an exception, the kilometres covered or the amount of goods may be taken into account in the calculation of additional remuneration if the method, conditions and rates of calculation thereof are such that they do not induce disregard of the rules for safe traffic and are prescribed in the collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(26.01.2000 j&otilde;ust.25.02.2000 - RT I 2000, 10, 59) </eesti>
<inglise>(26.01.2000 entered into force 25.02.2000 - RT I 2000, 10, 59) </inglise>
<eesti>IV peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter IV </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatised ja h&uuml;vitused </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees and Compensation </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatis lapse toitmise vaheaegade kasutamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantee for breaks for feeding child </inglise>
<eesti>Lapse toitmiseks t&ouml;&ouml;tajale seadusega etten&auml;htud vaheaegade eest s&auml;ilitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale keskmine palk riigieelarve vahenditest Sotsiaalministeeriumi eelarve kaudu sotsiaalministri kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Average wages for the breaks prescribed for employees by law for feeding a child shall be continued from state budget funds through the budget of the Ministry of Social Affairs pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Social Affairs. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.01.95 j&otilde;ust.01.01.95 - RT I 1995, 12, 120; 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.01.95 entered into force 01.01.95 - RT I 1995, 12, 120; 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatised rasedale s&uuml;nnituseelseks l&auml;bivaatuseks </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees for ante-natal examination to pregnant women </inglise>
<eesti>Rasedale, kellele t&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud andma arsti otsuses n&auml;idatud vaba aega s&uuml;nnituseelseks l&auml;bivaatuseks, s&auml;ilitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;taja keskmine palk. </eesti>
<inglise>Average wages shall be continued for pregnant woman to whom an employer is required to grant free time for ante-natal examination indicated in a decision of a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Tervisekontrollile suunatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja tagatised </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees to employee sent for health examination </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes seoses oma t&ouml;&ouml;ga on kohustatud l&auml;bima tervisekontrolli, s&auml;ilitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja tervisekontrolli l&auml;biviimise aja eest t&ouml;&ouml;taja keskmise palga. </eesti>
<inglise>The employer shall continue the average wages of an employee who is required to pass a health examination due to his or her work for time spent on the health examination. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatised taseme- ja t&ouml;&ouml;alase koolituse puhul </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees in case of further education and vocational training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tasemekoolitusega seotud &otilde;ppepuhkusel viibivale t&ouml;&ouml;tajale s&auml;ilitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja vastavalt t&auml;iskasvanute koolituse seaduse (RT I 1993, 74, 1054; 1998, 71, 1200; 1999, 10, 150; 60, 617) &sect; 8 5. l&otilde;ikele keskmise palga 10 p&auml;evaks ja maksab &uuml;lej&auml;&auml;nud &otilde;ppepuhkuse p&auml;evade eest palka v&auml;hemalt kehtiva palga alamm&auml;&auml;ra ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Pursuant to subsection 8 (5) of the Adult Education Act (RT I 1993, 74, 1054; 1998, 71, 1200; 1999, 10, 150; 60, 617), an employer shall continue to pay an employee who is on study leave to acquire formal education within the adult education system the employee's average wages for ten days and shall pay at least the established amount of the minimum wage for the rest of the days of study leave. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;alase koolitusega seotud &otilde;ppepuhkusel viibivale t&ouml;&ouml;tajale s&auml;ilitab t&ouml;&ouml;andja vastavalt t&auml;iskasvanute koolituse seaduse &sect; 8 6. l&otilde;ikele keskmise palga v&auml;hemalt 14 p&auml;evaks aastas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Pursuant to subsection 8 (6) of the Adult Education Act, an employer shall pay an employee who is on study leave for work-related training the employee's average wages for at least fourteen days per year. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetuse tagatised ja h&uuml;vitused </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees and compensation for business trips </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetusse saadetud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale s&auml;ilitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;koht ja tagatakse keskmine palk. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee sent on a business trip shall be guaranteed his or her position and average wages. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetusse saadetule h&uuml;vitatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person sent on a business trip shall be compensated for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) s&otilde;idukulud t&ouml;&ouml;kohast l&auml;hetuskohta ja tagasi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) return travel expenses between the workplace and the destination; </inglise>
<eesti>2) majutuskulud l&auml;hetuspaigas; </eesti>
<inglise>2) accommodation costs at the destination; </inglise>
<eesti>3) muud l&auml;hetus&uuml;lesande t&auml;itmisega seotud kulud ning </eesti>
<inglise>3) other expenses relating to the business assignment; and </inglise>
<eesti>4) makstakse p&auml;evaraha teeloleku ja l&auml;hetuskohas viibimise aja eest. </eesti>
<inglise>4) shall be paid a daily allowance for time spent on travel and at the destination. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;l&auml;hetuse h&uuml;vituste ja p&auml;evaraha alamm&auml;&auml;rad ning maksmise tingimused m&auml;&auml;rab kindlaks Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The minimum rates and terms of payment of compensation for business trips and daily allowances shall be determined by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&auml;hetataval on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt avanssi l&auml;hetuskulude katteks l&auml;hetuskulude ligikaudses suuruses. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who is sent on a business trip has the right to demand advance payment of the approximate amount of business trip expenses from the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>Avansi mittesaamisel v&otilde;ib l&auml;hetatav keelduda l&auml;hetusest. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person who is sent on a business trip does not receive advance payment, he or she may refuse to go on the business trip. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. (Kehtetu - 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. (Repealed - 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;vitised t&ouml;&ouml;raamatu andmisega ja l&otilde;pparve maksmisega viivitamise aja eest </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for time of delay upon return of employment record book and payment of final settlement </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;raamatu andmisega ja l&otilde;pparve maksmisega viivitamise aja eest on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma t&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitist keskmise palga ulatuses Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduses (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer is required to pay compensation for the time of delay upon return of employment record book and payment of final settlement to the extent of the average salary pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32; 1998, 111, 1829; 1999, 16, 276; 60, 616; 2000, 25, 144; 51, 327; 57, 370; 102, 669; 2001, 17, 78; 42, 233). </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Tagatised t&ouml;&ouml;tajate riiklike v&otilde;i omavalitsuslike kohustuste t&auml;itmise ajaks </eesti>
<inglise>Guarantees to employees for period of performance of state or local government duties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui riiklike v&otilde;i omavalitsuslike &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine seaduse v&otilde;i haldusakti kohaselt toimub t&ouml;&ouml;ajal, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud vabastama t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;st nende kohustuste t&auml;itmise ajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If, pursuant to law or administrative legislation, state or local government duties are performed during working time, the employer is required to exempt the employee from work for the period of performance of the duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise t&otilde;ttu kaotatud t&ouml;&ouml;tasu h&uuml;vitab t&ouml;&ouml;tajale vastav riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse organ t&ouml;&ouml;taja keskmise palga ulatuses, kui seaduse v&otilde;i kollektiivlepinguga ei ole ette n&auml;htud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Remuneration lost due to exemption from work prescribed in subsection (1) of this section shall be compensated to the employee by a corresponding state or local government authority to the extent of the average wages of the employee, unless otherwise prescribed by law or a collective agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>V peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter V </inglise>
<eesti>Palga arvutamine ja maksmine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation and Payment of Wages </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga maksmise kord ja t&auml;htajad </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure and due dates for payment of wages </inglise>
<eesti>Palgaarvestusaeg, palga maksmise kord ja t&auml;htajad m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks kollektiivlepingus, t&ouml;&ouml;sisekorra eeskirjas v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus. </eesti>
<inglise>The calculation period, procedure and due dates for payment of wages shall be determined in a collective agreement, internal work procedure rules or an employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Palka makstakse v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks kord kuus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) Wages shall be paid at least once a month. </inglise>
<eesti>(18.02.99 j&otilde;ust.01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 04.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </eesti>
<inglise>(18.02.99 entered into force 01.04.99 - RT I 1999, 29, 397; 04.04.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Palka makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;kohas ja t&ouml;&ouml;ajal, v&auml;lja arvatud, kui palk v&otilde;i selle osa kantakse t&ouml;&ouml;taja kirjaliku avalduse alusel t&ouml;&ouml;taja poolt osutatud pangakontole v&otilde;i kui kollektiiv- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Wages shall be paid to employees at the workplace and during working time unless the wages or a part thereof is transferred, based on the written application of the employee, to a bank account indicated by the employee, or unless otherwise agreed in the collective or employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga v&otilde;i selle osa &uuml;lekandmise kulud kannab t&ouml;&ouml;andja, kui ei ole kokku lepitud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>Transfer of wages or part thereof shall be borne by an employer unless agreed otherwise. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;taja kirjaliku avalduse alusel palga v&otilde;i selle osa &uuml;le kandma t&ouml;&ouml;taja poolt n&auml;idatud pangakontole. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On the basis of a written application of an employee, an employer is required to transfer wages or a part thereof to the bank account indicated by the employee. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) (Kehtetu - 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(4) (Repealed - 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Palk arvutatakse kogu palgaarvestusaja kestel tehtud ja t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt vastuv&otilde;etud t&ouml;&ouml; eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Wages shall be calculated for work performed and accepted by an employer during the entire wage calculation period. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml; eest, mille tegemine &uuml;letab palgaarvestusaja, makstakse palka v&otilde;rdeliselt t&ouml;&ouml; valmiduse astmega, kuid mitte v&auml;hem, kui on t&ouml;&ouml;lepingus kokkulepitud palgam&auml;&auml;ra alusel t&ouml;&ouml;l oldud aja eest arvutatud palk. </eesti>
<inglise>Work performed during a period which continues past the wage calculation period shall be paid for in proportion to the degree of completion of the work, but not less than in the amount of wages calculated for the time worked on the basis of the wage rate agreed in an employment contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) (Kehtetu - 04.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </eesti>
<inglise>(6) (Repealed - 04.04.2001 entered into force 01.01.2002 - RT I 2001, 42, 233) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>L&otilde;pparve maksmise t&auml;htaeg </eesti>
<inglise>Due date for payment of final settlement </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja on kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;eval t&ouml;&ouml;tajale maksma k&otilde;ik t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt saada olevad summad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer is required to pay all amounts due to an employee on the day an employment contract is terminated. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja ei saanud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;ppemise p&auml;eval l&otilde;pparvet vastu v&otilde;tta, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud maksma l&otilde;pparve viie p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates n&otilde;ude esitamisele j&auml;rgnenud p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>If an employee is unable to receive the final settlement on the day the employment contract is terminated, the employer is required to pay the final settlement within five days from the day following the day a claim is submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) (Kehtetu - 16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(2) (Repealed - 16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Palga maksmine palgap&auml;eva langemise korral puhkep&auml;evale </eesti>
<inglise>Payment of wages if pay day falls on day off </inglise>
<eesti>Kui palgap&auml;ev langeb puhkep&auml;evale, on t&ouml;&ouml;andja kohustatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajale palga maksma v&otilde;i &uuml;le kandma t&ouml;&ouml;taja pangakontole puhkep&auml;evale eelneval t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>If pay day falls on a day off, an employer is required to pay or transfer the wages to an employee's bank account on the working day preceding the day off. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Arvutamata v&otilde;i etten&auml;htust v&auml;hem arvutatud palga ja h&uuml;vituse n&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Claiming uncalculated or miscalculated wages and compensation </inglise>
<eesti>Kui t&ouml;&ouml;tajale ei ole palka v&otilde;i h&uuml;vitust arvutatud v&otilde;i neid on arvutatud v&auml;hem, on t&ouml;&ouml;tajal &otilde;igus esitada n&otilde;ue individuaalse t&ouml;&ouml;vaidluse lahendamise seaduses (RT I 1996, 3, 57; 2000, 25, 144) etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>If wages or compensation are not calculated for an employee or they are miscalculated in a lower amount, an employee has the right to file a claim pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Individual Labour Dispute Resolution Act (RT I 1996, 3, 57; 2000, 25, 144). </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja vastutus palga maksmise v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmisega viivitamise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of employer for delay in payment or transfer of wages </inglise>
<eesti>Palga maksmisega v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja pangakontole &uuml;lekandmisega viivitamise eest maksab t&ouml;&ouml;andja t&ouml;&ouml;tajale iga viivitatud p&auml;eva eest viivist 0,5% maksmisele v&otilde;i &uuml;lekandmisele kuulunud palgast. </eesti>
<inglise>An employer shall pay a penalty to an employee for delay in payment or transfer of wages to the employee's bank account in the amount of 0.5 per cent of the payable or transferable wages for each day of delay. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>VI peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter VI </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnipidamised palgast </eesti>
<inglise>Deductions from wages </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnipidamised palgast </eesti>
<inglise>Deductions from wages </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja palgast v&otilde;ib ilma tema n&otilde;usolekuta seadusega etten&auml;htud alusel, korras ja ulatuses kinni pidada: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following may be deducted from an employee's wages without the consent of the employee on the basis, pursuant to procedure and to the extent provided by law: </inglise>
<eesti>1) seadusega kehtestatud makse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) taxes established by law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tasu v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamata puhkusep&auml;evade eest t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel enne selle t&ouml;&ouml;aasta l&otilde;ppu, mille arvel t&ouml;&ouml;taja juba oli puhkuse saanud, v&auml;lja arvatud t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse &sect;-des 82 ja 85 ning &sect; 86 punktides 1, 2, 3, 4, 9 ja 10 etten&auml;htud alustel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) remuneration for holiday days upon termination of an employment contract before the end of a working year for which an employee has already received holiday, except upon termination of an employment contract on the bases prescribed by &sect;&sect; 82 and 85 and clauses 86 1), 2), 3), 4), 9) and 10) of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) muid seadusega etten&auml;htud summasid. </eesti>
<inglise>3) other amounts prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;taja palgast kinni pidada t&ouml;&ouml;andjale t&auml;htajaks tagastamata avansse, t&ouml;&ouml;tajale arvutusvea t&otilde;ttu liigselt makstud summasid ja t&ouml;&ouml;taja eelneval kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul t&ouml;&ouml;taja poolt t&ouml;&ouml;andjale tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamise summasid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An employer may deduct advance payments not duly repaid to the employer, amounts paid in excess to an employee due to a calculation error and, with the prior written consent of the employee, compensation for damage caused by the employee to the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&otilde;igi palgale p&ouml;&ouml;ratud n&otilde;uete alusel kinnipidamise korral peab t&ouml;&ouml;tajale maksmiseks v&otilde;i tema pangakontole &uuml;lekandmiseks j&auml;&auml;ma v&auml;hemalt summa, mis vastab 80%-le riigi poolt kehtestatud palga alamm&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) After deductions are made on the basis of all claims against wages, the amount payable to an employee or transferred to his or her bank account must equal at least 80 per cent of the minimum wage rate established by the state. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.05.2001 j&otilde;ust.11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.05.2001 entered into force 11.06.2001 - RT I 2001, 50, 287) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Palga piisamatuse korral rahuldatakse n&otilde;uded seaduses etten&auml;htud j&auml;rjekorras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Upon insufficiency of wages, the claims shall be satisfied in the order prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;lepingu l&otilde;petamisel t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse &sect;-de 82 lg. 2, 84 lg. 1, 87 lg. 2, 90, 110 lg. 3 ja 113 lg. 3 v&otilde;i t&auml;iendavalt kollektiivlepingu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt makstavatest h&uuml;vitustest on lubatud kinni pidada seadusega kehtestatud maksud, k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktis 2 ja 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud tasu v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamata puhkusep&auml;evade eest ja tagastamata avansid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon termination of an employment contract, taxes established by law, alimony, remuneration for holiday days specified in clause (1) 2) and subsection (2) of this section and the advance payments which have not been repaid may be deducted from the compensation payable by an employer pursuant to subsections 82 (2), 84 (1), and 87 (2), &sect; 90, subsections 110 (3) and 113 (3) of the Employment Contracts Act or additionally on the basis of a collective agreement. </inglise>
